Look!

1066
01:33:14,600 --> 01:33:16,920
- The Zeppelin!
- We've found Grandpa.

1067
01:33:17,000 --> 01:33:18,880
Not yet we haven't.

1068
01:33:34,760 --> 01:33:36,960
What's happening?

1069
01:33:37,080 --> 01:33:39,760
- Remarkable!
- Your Excellency...

1070
01:33:39,880 --> 01:33:42,080
- We are being attacked.
- Attacked?

1071
01:33:42,160 --> 01:33:43,520
Attack! Attack!

1072
01:33:43,760 --> 01:33:46,480
That was that terrible Bomburst!

1073
01:33:46,600 --> 01:33:48,880
It certainly was.

1074
01:33:49,000 --> 01:33:51,040
- Where are they going?
- It's a car!

1075
01:33:51,160 --> 01:33:52,520
Where did they go?

1076
01:33:54,640 --> 01:33:57,240
How floaty in the heavenly abode,
fully peoplebodies.

1077
01:34:00,400 --> 01:34:00,760
Fire!

1078
01:34:00,880 --> 01:34:04,560
What's the matter with you?
You want to destroy my beautiful car?

1079
01:34:05,160 --> 01:34:07,000
They're firing at us.

1080
01:34:07,120 --> 01:34:10,400
There are children up there.

1081
01:34:10,480 --> 01:34:12,440
We'd better get away from here.

1082
01:34:14,360 --> 01:34:17,560
Hang on, everybody.
We're coming in to land.

1083
01:34:17,640 --> 01:34:21,280
Your Excellency,
it's landing in the village.

1084
01:34:21,360 --> 01:34:23,680
Call out the guards!

1085
01:34:33,160 --> 01:34:35,080
And call out the child catcher!

1086
01:34:41,200 --> 01:34:42,400
Charge!

1087
01:34:47,640 --> 01:34:48,800
Charge!

1088
01:34:53,000 --> 01:34:54,440
Let me in.

1089
01:35:05,800 --> 01:35:08,160
We made it!

1090
01:35:10,400 --> 01:35:12,400
- Isn't Chitty wonderful?
- You're clever, Daddy.

1091
01:35:12,480 --> 01:35:14,880
Yes, he certainly is.

1092
01:35:15,000 --> 01:35:17,200
You all stay here.
I'm going to the castle.

1093
01:35:17,320 --> 01:35:19,720
- We want to come too.
- To help you find Grandpa.

1094
01:35:19,800 --> 01:35:22,480
Don't you think
we ought to stay together?

1095
01:35:22,600 --> 01:35:25,640
- Maybe you're right.
- Come on, children.

1096
01:35:28,360 --> 01:35:30,640
- I wonder where we are.
- I don't know.

1097
01:35:31,240 --> 01:35:32,840
Come on.

1098
01:35:36,920 --> 01:35:39,880
Pardon me, sir. The castle?

1099
01:35:40,000 --> 01:35:42,800
- Le chateau?
- Der Schloss?

1100
01:35:44,360 --> 01:35:47,320
What's the matter with him?

1101
01:35:47,400 --> 01:35:49,400
Come on.

1102
01:36:18,800 --> 01:36:21,640
What are they staring at?

1103
01:36:21,760 --> 01:36:23,920
I don't know.

1104
01:36:26,600 --> 01:36:28,880
It seems to be the children.

1105
01:36:29,000 --> 01:36:31,960
Haven't they seen children before?

1106
01:36:33,520 --> 01:36:35,680
Haven't you noticed?

1107
01:36:35,800 --> 01:36:38,040
There aren't any children.

1108
01:36:39,240 --> 01:36:41,000
Not one.

1109
01:36:46,440 --> 01:36:48,480
What's going on?

1110
01:36:51,000 --> 01:36:53,720
Hey, you, what's happening?

1111
01:36:54,120 --> 01:36:55,680
Soldiers! Soldiers!

1112
01:37:04,160 --> 01:37:06,120
Hey, you there!

1113
01:37:06,200 --> 01:37:09,360
- Get the children in here.
- Can you tell me what's happening?

1114
01:37:09,440 --> 01:37:11,640
Quickly, before the soldiers get here.

1115
01:37:11,760 --> 01:37:16,360
Come, Fraulein.
Get inside, quickly.

1116
01:37:17,800 --> 01:37:22,440
We must hide the children.
The soldiers will take them away.

1117
01:37:22,560 --> 01:37:24,160
But why?

1118
01:37:24,240 --> 01:37:26,960
Nobody's allowed
to have children in Vulgaria.

1119
01:37:27,080 --> 01:37:31,960
- But what about all these toys?
- The baroness hates children.

1120
01:37:32,080 --> 01:37:35,280
Quickly, down there.
And don't make a sound.

1121
01:37:54,120 --> 01:37:58,240
I want every house in this square
to be searched from top to bottom.

1122
01:37:58,360 --> 01:38:00,480
First section, step out there and search.

1123
01:38:00,600 --> 01:38:04,840
Second section, over there.
Section three, over there.

1124
01:38:06,240 --> 01:38:08,320
Search everywhere!

1125
01:38:11,360 --> 01:38:12,880
Giddap!

1126
01:38:18,200 --> 01:38:22,520
There are children here somewhere.

1127
01:38:22,640 --> 01:38:25,680
I can smell them.

1128
01:38:26,360 --> 01:38:28,480
Aaah-ha!

1129
01:38:29,520 --> 01:38:31,120
Captain!

1130
01:38:31,200 --> 01:38:34,200
I think we've got them.

1131
01:38:34,320 --> 01:38:37,920
- Lieutenant!
- Break down this door.

1132
01:38:38,800 --> 01:38:40,560
Get this door open.

1133
01:38:40,640 --> 01:38:42,320
All right. I'm coming.

1134
01:38:42,400 --> 01:38:45,080
Bang the door down! Quickly!

1135
01:38:46,080 --> 01:38:48,360
You've no right to come in here!

1136
01:38:48,440 --> 01:38:50,960
- Search the place!
- Search! Search!

1137
01:38:53,080 --> 01:38:55,000
A- ha!

1138
01:38:55,400 --> 01:38:58,040
They are here somewhere.

1139
01:38:58,160 --> 01:39:00,840
I can feel it in my bones.

1140
01:39:00,920 --> 01:39:03,800
There are children here.

1141
01:39:03,880 --> 01:39:08,200
Children in a toy shop.
Such a notion. I mean...

1142
01:39:08,320 --> 01:39:11,720
What are you doing?
That's for the baron's birthday.

1143
01:39:11,800 --> 01:39:15,160
Let me tell you, toymaker.

1144
01:39:15,240 --> 01:39:19,600
This nose of mine has never failed me.

1145
01:39:19,680 --> 01:39:24,720
And if there are children here, my friend,

1146
01:39:24,800 --> 01:39:28,160
you will die.

1147
01:39:32,160 --> 01:39:34,120
A- ha!

1148
01:39:36,920 --> 01:39:40,520
Quick, open it up.
Get down there and search the cellar.

1149
01:39:43,640 --> 01:39:46,640
The baroness will have
your teeth for a necklace

1150
01:39:46,760 --> 01:39:49,680
and your eyeballs for earrings.

1151
01:39:49,800 --> 01:39:55,200
- Nobody down here.
- Fool. Idiot. Out of my way.

1152
01:39:55,320 --> 01:39:59,320
You have to know where to look.

1153
01:39:59,400 --> 01:40:03,640
Like cockroaches
they get under the floors,

1154
01:40:03,760 --> 01:40:06,160
in the cracks in the walls,

1155
01:40:06,240 --> 01:40:09,040
in the woodwork.

1156
01:40:45,640 --> 01:40:49,560
I don't trust a man who makes toys

1157
01:40:49,640 --> 01:40:54,480
in a land where children are forbidden.

1158
01:40:54,600 --> 01:40:57,760
Every toy I make is exclusively
for His Excellency the Baron.

1159
01:40:57,880 --> 01:41:01,720
Captain, ze flying car.
We've captured ze flying car.

1160
01:41:01,800 --> 01:41:03,480
Fall in! Fall in!

1161
01:41:22,120 --> 01:41:24,160
Take zis car to the castle.

1162
01:41:27,440 --> 01:41:31,480
- They can't take Chitty.
- Daddy, do something.

1163
01:41:31,600 --> 01:41:34,600
- What are you going to do?
- I'm not just gonna stand here.

1164
01:41:34,680 --> 01:41:38,720
Are you mad? Are you going to take on
the whole army single-handed?

1165
01:41:46,360 --> 01:41:48,800
What kind of a country is this?

1166
01:41:48,880 --> 01:41:50,720
No children.

1167
01:41:50,800 --> 01:41:53,280
Everybody terrified out of their lives.

1168
01:41:53,360 --> 01:41:55,760
My friend, take some good advice.

1169
01:41:55,880 --> 01:41:59,680
Take your children and your good lady
and get out of Vulgaria.

1170
01:41:59,800 --> 01:42:04,080
And leave Grandpa up in the castle?
We need to get him out.

1171
01:42:04,160 --> 01:42:07,160
- Just tell me how to get there.
- I'm only a toymaker.

1172
01:42:07,240 --> 01:42:11,320
If I don't finish this for the baron's
birthday, I shall be a dead toymaker.

1173
01:42:11,400 --> 01:42:14,720
I'll go myself.
Truly, you stay here with the children.

1174
01:42:14,800 --> 01:42:16,800
All right, all right.

1175
01:42:20,200 --> 01:42:23,880
You don't know
what you're letting yourself in for.

1176
01:42:25,240 --> 01:42:28,960
- Here's one for you, one for you.
- Thank you, toymaker.

1177
01:42:29,080 --> 01:42:31,240
Keep them out of sight, please.

1178
01:42:31,360 --> 01:42:33,440
You be good and do what Truly tells you.

1179
01:42:33,560 --> 01:42:35,200
- We will.
- Yes, Daddy.

1180
01:42:35,640 --> 01:42:38,320
Are you coming?

1181
01:42:50,480 --> 01:42:51,680
Come.

1182
01:42:57,760 --> 01:43:00,080
Quickly!

1183
01:43:03,760 --> 01:43:06,120
There isn't a scrap of food in the place.

1184
01:43:06,200 --> 01:43:10,520
- I'm so hungry, my tummy hurts.
- Mine is making funny noises.

1185
01:43:10,640 --> 01:43:12,960
I simply must find something for you.

1186
01:43:13,080 --> 01:43:15,720
Promise not to move
from here until I come back.

1187
01:43:15,800 --> 01:43:17,880
- We promise, don't we?
- Yes.

1188
01:43:18,000 --> 01:43:20,720
Remember, you stay right here.

1189
01:43:26,800 --> 01:43:30,600
To get in that way,
you have to be a mouse, or a magician.

1190
01:43:36,680 --> 01:43:39,800
We should go down now
before a sentry sees us.

1191
01:43:39,880 --> 01:43:42,080
Come. Come.

1192
01:43:45,400 --> 01:43:47,400
The flying car.

1193
01:43:48,480 --> 01:43:51,560
At last it's mine.

1194
01:43:51,640 --> 01:43:54,640
Send for the inventor.

1195
01:43:55,160 --> 01:43:57,160
Now, then, fly.

1196
01:43:57,240 --> 01:43:59,000
- Yes, fly.
- Fly.

1197
01:43:59,120 --> 01:44:01,160
- Come on. Fly.
- Fly, fly, fly.

1198
01:44:02,160 --> 01:44:04,160
I command you to fly!

1199
01:44:05,360 --> 01:44:06,080
Watch it.

1200
01:44:06,160 --> 01:44:09,160
- Over here.
- Hello! What's this doing here?

1201
01:44:09,240 --> 01:44:12,760
You are the inventor.
Make this car fly.

1202
01:44:12,880 --> 01:44:16,160
Make it fly. Go on. Get in.

1203
01:44:18,560 --> 01:44:21,480
Stand back, everyone.
We are going to fly.

1204
01:44:21,600 --> 01:44:24,600
Yoo-hoo, Bombie, wait for me!

1205
01:44:24,680 --> 01:44:27,960
Every time I want to have
a little fun, she turns up.

1206
01:44:30,760 --> 01:44:33,640
My darling, we are going for a fly.

1207
01:44:33,760 --> 01:44:37,720
How exciting. Fly. How thrilling.

1208
01:44:37,800 --> 01:44:40,840
- Hurry up.
- I am doing my best, sir.

1209
01:44:40,920 --> 01:44:43,840
Just a minute.
Here's one we haven't tried.

1210
01:44:43,920 --> 01:44:46,480
- Here we go, my beloved.
- Hold on!

1211
01:44:48,160 --> 01:44:50,840
Isn't it exciting, my dear?

1212
01:44:56,200 --> 01:44:59,040
You are a genius.
Bring my guns.

1213
01:44:59,160 --> 01:45:01,920
Don't worry, little pigeon.
I'll get you down.

1214
01:45:02,000 --> 01:45:05,440
I've been waiting for this for 20 years.

1215
01:45:06,120 --> 01:45:09,440
Are you still there, my love?
Don't move.

1216
01:45:18,080 --> 01:45:20,800
There she is, Your Excellency.

1217
01:45:20,880 --> 01:45:23,040
My diamonds!

1218
01:45:23,160 --> 01:45:25,360
Are you all right, my dear?

1219
01:45:26,000 --> 01:45:28,520
I'm all right, my dumpling.

1220
01:45:29,160 --> 01:45:32,360
Good. Never mind.
I'll get her the next time.

1221
01:45:47,800 --> 01:45:53,120
Here we are, children.
Come and get your lollipops.

1222
01:45:55,000 --> 01:45:56,600
Lollipops.

1223
01:45:56,680 --> 01:45:59,400
Come along, my little ones.

1224
01:45:59,520 --> 01:46:01,480
Lollipops.

1225
01:46:04,680 --> 01:46:08,880
Ice cream. Chocolate.
All free today.

1226
01:46:09,000 --> 01:46:11,040
Listen.

1227
01:46:13,200 --> 01:46:14,600
What's that?

1228
01:46:18,560 --> 01:46:22,280
Children, where are you?

1229
01:46:23,520 --> 01:46:26,960
I know you're here somewhere.

1230
01:46:28,640 --> 01:46:33,200
I've lots of lovely goodies for you.

1231
01:46:33,320 --> 01:46:35,880
Jeremy, you mustn't.

1232
01:46:39,320 --> 01:46:41,280
Lollipops.

1233
01:46:42,120 --> 01:46:46,320
And all free today.

1234
01:46:46,400 --> 01:46:48,080
Cherry pies,

1235
01:46:48,160 --> 01:46:50,200
cream puffs,

1236
01:46:50,320 --> 01:46:51,920
ice cream,

1237
01:46:52,000 --> 01:46:53,800
treacle tarts.

1238
01:46:53,880 --> 01:46:56,680
- Treacle tarts.
- And ice creams.

1239
01:46:56,800 --> 01:46:58,360
And all free.

1240
01:46:58,440 --> 01:47:02,240
Come along, kiddiwinkies.

1241
01:47:02,760 --> 01:47:06,120
- Come on.
- Truly said we mustn't.

1242
01:47:06,200 --> 01:47:09,240
We'll get Truly some as well.

1243
01:47:12,600 --> 01:47:14,520
Mr Man...

1244
01:47:15,160 --> 01:47:18,000
Children, come back.

1245
01:47:20,560 --> 01:47:22,520
Children, come back here.

1246
01:47:25,600 --> 01:47:27,520
Come along, my little dears,

1247
01:47:27,640 --> 01:47:29,400
my little mice.

1248
01:47:29,520 --> 01:47:31,480
Come to me.

1249
01:47:32,320 --> 01:47:34,880
What will it be? Ice cream?

1250
01:47:34,920 --> 01:47:39,040
Strawberry, chocolate, vanilla.
It's all inside.

1251
01:47:39,160 --> 01:47:41,200
Come along, my little dears.

1252
01:47:41,320 --> 01:47:43,640
Not a penny to pay.

1253
01:47:43,760 --> 01:47:46,480
Go inside, my little dears.

1254
01:48:05,800 --> 01:48:07,480
Children!

1255
01:48:11,760 --> 01:48:13,360
Truly.

1256
01:48:13,440 --> 01:48:14,920
Help! Help!

1257
01:48:15,000 --> 01:48:18,400
- What's happened?
- He took the children.

1258
01:48:23,160 --> 01:48:26,000
Your Excellency.

1259
01:48:26,120 --> 01:48:28,680
- Let us out.
- Silence.

1260
01:48:39,200 --> 01:48:42,120
Children, Your Highness.

1261
01:48:42,200 --> 01:48:46,560
Foreign children. Unique specimens.

1262
01:48:46,640 --> 01:48:49,000
You're sure they can't get out?

1263
01:48:49,120 --> 01:48:51,080
No, Your Highness.

1264
01:48:52,160 --> 01:48:57,080
Perhaps Your Highness
would care to examine them.

1265
01:48:57,160 --> 01:49:02,440
Nasty little creatures.
Very, very treacherous. Foreign.

1266
01:49:04,480 --> 01:49:10,280
- Wait till our daddy hears about this.
- He'll blow up the whole castle.

1267
01:49:10,360 --> 01:49:13,360
Take them away to the tower.

1268
01:49:14,400 --> 01:49:16,600
You're a nasty, horrid, mean old lady.

1269
01:49:16,680 --> 01:49:19,640
And very ugly.

1270
01:49:19,760 --> 01:49:22,120
Oh, she's going.

1271
01:49:48,000 --> 01:49:52,960
200 feet above us through that solid rock
is the castle of Baron Bomburst.

1272
01:50:23,160 --> 01:50:25,160
These are our children.

1273
01:50:25,240 --> 01:50:30,120
For five years, we have hidden them here.

1274
01:50:30,200 --> 01:50:35,800
They don't know what a tree looks like
or what it is to run in the sunshine.

1275
01:50:37,800 --> 01:50:39,800
Food.

1276
01:50:39,880 --> 01:50:42,280
There's bread for everyone.

1277
01:50:42,360 --> 01:50:48,360
Like little rats, they run up and down the
sewers, stealing food from the kitchens.

1278
01:50:48,440 --> 01:50:50,680
Here, catch!

1279
01:50:50,800 --> 01:50:53,080
Son!

1280
01:50:53,640 --> 01:50:57,520
I think my children are up there
in the castle with their grandfather.

1281
01:50:57,640 --> 01:51:00,280
- Have you seen them?
- No, sir.

1282
01:51:00,360 --> 01:51:02,280
- A little boy and girl?
- Yes.

1283
01:51:02,360 --> 01:51:04,480
They're locked up in the tower.

1284
01:51:04,600 --> 01:51:07,880
- And the grandfather?
- In the dungeon.

1285
01:51:08,000 --> 01:51:10,800
Sir, have you come to help us?

1286
01:51:15,600 --> 01:51:18,560
Are you going to take us out of here?

1287
01:51:20,320 --> 01:51:24,040
- What's your name, son?
- Peter, sir.

1288
01:51:24,160 --> 01:51:29,400
Peter, you shouldn't be afraid,
even in a terrible place like this.

1289
01:51:29,520 --> 01:51:33,080
Because there's always hope.

1290
01:51:33,160 --> 01:51:37,760
That's what I always tell my children
when they're afraid.

1291
01:51:41,880 --> 01:51:48,560
## A gentle breeze
from Hushabye Mountain

1292
01:51:48,640 --> 01:51:56,040
## Softly blows o'er Lullaby Bay

1293
01:51:56,160 --> 01:52:02,680
## It fills the sails
of boats that are waiting

1294
01:52:02,800 --> 01:52:06,960
## Waiting to sail...

1295
01:52:09,320 --> 01:52:18,080
## So close your eyes
on Hushabye Mountain

1296
01:52:18,160 --> 01:52:25,080
## Wave goodbye
to cares of the day

1297
01:52:25,160 --> 01:52:34,120
## And watch your boat
from Hushabye Mountain

1298
01:52:34,200 --> 01:52:46,920
## Sail far away from Lullaby Bay

1299
01:52:48,600 --> 01:52:51,720
Is that the only advice
you have to offer?

1300
01:52:51,800 --> 01:52:57,120
It's a beautiful dream, but I don't see
how it's going to help them.

1301
01:52:57,200 --> 01:53:00,200
We're gonna get up into that castle.

1302
01:53:00,320 --> 01:53:03,000
- It is impossible.
- We'll see.

1303
01:53:03,120 --> 01:53:05,520
Everybody listen to me.

1304
01:53:05,640 --> 01:53:09,080
- You want to get out of here, don't you?
- Yes!

1305
01:53:10,120 --> 01:53:12,880
Tomorrow
is Baron Bomburst's birthday, yes?

1306
01:53:13,000 --> 01:53:14,960
Boo!

1307
01:53:16,240 --> 01:53:19,520
We'll give him a party he'll never forget.

1308
01:53:19,640 --> 01:53:23,800
Everybody gather around here.
I have an idea.

1309
01:53:36,120 --> 01:53:41,120
## Happy birthday to me

1310
01:53:41,200 --> 01:53:45,280
## Happy birthday, dear Bombie

1311
01:53:45,600 --> 01:53:47,600
Don't move.

1312
01:53:47,680 --> 01:53:49,760
What a picture.

1313
01:53:49,880 --> 01:53:52,200
Such memories it brings back.

1314
01:53:55,000 --> 01:53:56,680
My little dumpling.

1315
01:53:56,800 --> 01:53:58,960
My Liebling.

1316
01:53:59,080 --> 01:54:02,640
## You're my little chu-chi face

1317
01:54:02,760 --> 01:54:06,960
## My kootchi, kootchi,
wootchi little chu-chi face

1318
01:54:07,080 --> 01:54:13,440
## Every time I look at you I sigh

1319
01:54:14,160 --> 01:54:18,120
## And you're my little teddy bear

1320
01:54:18,200 --> 01:54:21,960
## My lovey, lovey dovey little teddy bear

1321
01:54:22,080 --> 01:54:28,240
## You're the Apfel Streudel of mein eye

1322
01:54:29,640 --> 01:54:33,520
## Your chu-chi, wootchi nose,
your chu-chi, wootchi eyes

1323
01:54:33,640 --> 01:54:37,200
## They set my heart a-flutter

1324
01:54:37,320 --> 01:54:41,200
## Your ootchi, kootchi ways,
your ootchi, kootchi gaze

1325
01:54:41,320 --> 01:54:48,200
## Wilts me down like meltings butter

1326
01:54:50,600 --> 01:54:53,760
## You're my little chu-chi face

1327
01:54:53,880 --> 01:54:58,080
## And you're my teddy bear

1328
01:54:58,160 --> 01:55:04,200
## Together we're a chu-chi, wootchi,
ootchi, kootchi pair

1329
01:55:21,200 --> 01:55:25,040
## Whatever you may ask
becomes my happy task

1330
01:55:25,160 --> 01:55:28,520
## I only live to serve you

1331
01:55:28,640 --> 01:55:32,640
## I never will divine
what magic made you mine

1332
01:55:32,760 --> 01:55:39,880
## I only know
I don't deserve you

1333
01:55:41,240 --> 01:55:43,240
Ha, ha, ha!

1334
01:55:47,800 --> 01:55:51,200
## You're my little chu-chi face

1335
01:55:51,320 --> 01:55:55,120
## And you're my teddy bear

1336
01:55:55,200 --> 01:55:59,800
## Together we're a chu-chi,
wootchi, ootchi, kootchi

1337
01:56:00,480 --> 01:56:02,160
- ## Chu-chi
- ## Wootchi

1338
01:56:02,240 --> 01:56:03,640
- ## Ootchi
- ## Kootchi

1339
01:56:04,360 --> 01:56:08,880
## Chu-chi, wootchi, ootchi, kootchi

1340
01:56:09,000 --> 01:56:10,960
## Pair

1341
01:57:01,320 --> 01:57:03,480
What a rotten birthday party.

1342
01:57:03,600 --> 01:57:06,600
Never mind, my little Bombie.

1343
01:57:06,680 --> 01:57:08,840
I have a surprise for you.

1344
01:57:08,920 --> 01:57:12,840
Surprises! Oh, I love surprises.

1345
01:57:12,920 --> 01:57:16,000
Sit down quickly.

1346
01:57:17,520 --> 01:57:22,560
Summon the toymaker.

1347
01:57:25,640 --> 01:57:28,440
Hurry up. Don't waste time.

1348
01:57:33,880 --> 01:57:38,360
Your Excellency, may I wish you all you
wish yourself on this happy occasion.

1349
01:57:38,440 --> 01:57:42,400
Never mind that.
What have you made me for my birthday?

1350
01:57:42,480 --> 01:57:47,400
What have I made you? Such a toy.
A work of mechanical perfection.

1351
01:57:47,520 --> 01:57:50,200
Where is it? Bring it in.

1352
01:57:50,320 --> 01:57:55,320
Right away. I'll get it for you.
Bring in the baron's birthday present.

1353
01:58:05,600 --> 01:58:09,920
This year, Your Excellency,
I have surpassed even myself.

1354
01:58:10,000 --> 01:58:14,160
Put it down there. Careful with it.

1355
01:58:14,240 --> 01:58:18,960
For months I have been working
night and day perfecting every little detail

1356
01:58:19,080 --> 01:58:21,800
to bring you this.

1357
01:58:25,000 --> 01:58:28,000
Dolls? Dolls?

1358
01:58:28,120 --> 01:58:32,200
I have hundreds of dolls.

1359
01:58:32,560 --> 01:58:37,760
But this is not just
an ordinary doll, Your Excellency.

1360
01:58:41,600 --> 01:58:43,560
You see?

1361
01:58:49,920 --> 01:58:56,080
## What do you see,
you people gazing at me

1362
01:58:57,400 --> 01:59:03,280
## You see a doll on a music box
that's wound by a key

1363
01:59:04,920 --> 01:59:11,360
## How can you tell
I'm under a spell

1364
01:59:11,440 --> 01:59:17,440
## I'm waiting for love's first kiss

1365
01:59:19,800 --> 01:59:27,320
## You cannot see
how much I long to be free

1366
01:59:27,400 --> 01:59:34,920
## Turning around on this music box
that's wound by a key

1367
01:59:35,000 --> 01:59:42,440
## Yearning, yearning

1368
01:59:42,560 --> 01:59:49,800
## While I'm turning around and around

1369
02:02:10,920 --> 02:02:13,400
- ## What do you see
- ## Truly Scrumptious

1370
02:02:13,520 --> 02:02:18,560
- ## You people gazing at me
- ## You're truly, truly scrumptious

1371
02:02:18,640 --> 02:02:21,720
- ## You see a doll on a music box
- ## Scrumptious as...

1372
02:02:21,800 --> 02:02:24,800
## That's wound by a key

1373
02:02:26,080 --> 02:02:28,840
## How can you tell

1374
02:02:28,920 --> 02:02:32,480
## I'm under a spell

1375
02:02:32,600 --> 02:02:36,400
- ## I'm waiting for love's
- ## Honest, Truly

1376
02:02:36,480 --> 02:02:41,080
- ## First kiss
- ## You're the answer to my wishes

1377
02:02:41,160 --> 02:02:43,520
- ## You cannot see
- ## Truly Scrumptious

1378
02:02:43,640 --> 02:02:48,600
- ## How much I long to be free
- ## Though I may seem presumptuous

1379
02:02:48,680 --> 02:02:51,960
- ## Turning around on this music box
- ## Ne...

1380
02:02:52,080 --> 02:02:55,120
## That's wound by a key

1381
02:02:55,880 --> 02:02:59,840
- ## Yearning
- ## My heart beats so unruly

1382
02:02:59,920 --> 02:03:03,360
- ## Yearning
- ## Because I love you truly

1383
02:03:03,760 --> 02:03:05,400
- ## While
- ## Honest

1384
02:03:05,520 --> 02:03:07,480
- ## I'm
- ## Truly, I do

1385
02:03:07,680 --> 02:03:09,960
## Turning around and around

1386
02:03:19,360 --> 02:03:21,560
Just a minute!

1387
02:03:50,000 --> 02:03:52,000
Atchoo!

1388
02:04:59,520 --> 02:05:01,360
Oh, I'm so happy

1389
02:05:01,440 --> 02:05:03,960
I could jump for joy!

1390
02:05:11,320 --> 02:05:13,600
- Come on.
- Come, follow me.

1391
02:05:14,600 --> 02:05:17,400
Children!

1392
02:05:28,200 --> 02:05:29,600
Get me down!

1393
02:05:43,680 --> 02:05:45,400
Call the cavalry!

1394
02:05:54,000 --> 02:05:57,640
- Jeremy, Jeremy!
- Jemima!

1395
02:06:00,600 --> 02:06:03,720
- They could be anywhere.
- Look that way. I'll go this way.

1396
02:06:15,600 --> 02:06:19,360
Jeremy and Jemima!
Jeremy and Jemima!

1397
02:06:19,440 --> 02:06:21,200
Jeremy! Jemima!

1398
02:06:21,320 --> 02:06:24,400
It's Truly. We're in here.

1399
02:06:24,480 --> 02:06:27,480
Don't worry.
We'll get you out of here.

1400
02:06:28,000 --> 02:06:30,560
Here. They're in there.

1401
02:06:30,640 --> 02:06:34,880
- Children, are you all right?
- Daddy, get us out of here!

1402
02:06:36,240 --> 02:06:40,000
We found them.
Help me break the door down.

1403
02:06:40,880 --> 02:06:43,200
Children, get away from the door.

1404
02:06:49,520 --> 02:06:52,160
- Children!
- Daddy! Daddy!

1405
02:07:36,800 --> 02:07:38,240
Let me down!

1406
02:07:40,800 --> 02:07:42,760
Ow!

1407
02:07:44,120 --> 02:07:48,320
- Mein Liebchen, are you hurt?
- My back is broken.

1408
02:07:48,400 --> 02:07:52,400
- We must escape through the cellars.
- Well, come on, hurry up.

1409
02:07:52,480 --> 02:07:54,480
Come on.

1410
02:07:56,600 --> 02:07:58,720
- You stay here.
- Daddy, where are you going?

1411
02:08:06,800 --> 02:08:11,240
Where are these children coming from?
We passed a law against children.

1412
02:08:11,360 --> 02:08:15,080
- This way. We'll go down here.
- Where are we going?

1413
02:08:15,160 --> 02:08:19,160
- I'll get my clothes dirty.
- Don't argue.

1414
02:08:28,000 --> 02:08:30,880
Oh, my crown! I lost my crown.

1415
02:08:31,000 --> 02:08:33,440
Never mind, my little Bombkin.

1416
02:08:41,360 --> 02:08:43,360
Here.

1417
02:08:44,240 --> 02:08:46,240
Attack!

1418
02:08:47,000 --> 02:08:49,960
- Daddy, look out.
- Look, there's Chitty.

1419
02:08:50,080 --> 02:08:52,160
She's come to save us.

1420
02:09:09,640 --> 02:09:13,800
Hello. What's that car doing here?

1421
02:09:14,320 --> 02:09:17,080
There's Grandpa.

1422
02:09:17,160 --> 02:09:18,960
Caractacus!

1423
02:09:48,920 --> 02:09:52,280
Stand back from the propellers.
Keep clear.

1424
02:10:05,640 --> 02:10:09,360
And so, after that,
Vulgaria became a free country.

1425
02:10:09,440 --> 02:10:14,000
And all the children laughed
and played and they were very happy.

1426
02:10:14,400 --> 02:10:18,720
And Chitty flew high
over the mountains back to England,

1427
02:10:18,800 --> 02:10:20,760
everybody safe and sound and...

1428
02:10:20,880 --> 02:10:25,200
- And Daddy and Truly were married.
- And lived happily ever after.

1429
02:10:25,680 --> 02:10:28,680
Is that how the story ends?

1430
02:10:30,640 --> 02:10:35,000
It's getting late. We'd better get back.

1431
02:11:00,880 --> 02:11:02,240
Well...

1432
02:11:02,360 --> 02:11:04,800
- Goodbye, Jeremy, Jemima.
- Goodbye, Truly.

1433
02:11:04,880 --> 02:11:07,560
- Will we see you again?
- I expect so.

1434
02:11:07,640 --> 02:11:09,640
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

1435
02:11:13,360 --> 02:11:15,320
Truly!

1436
02:11:16,680 --> 02:11:19,680
I hope the children didn't embarrass you.

1437
02:11:19,800 --> 02:11:22,920
- In what way?
- That silly joke about us getting married.

1438
02:11:23,000 --> 02:11:25,040
- You know what kids are like.
- I understand.

1439
02:11:25,160 --> 02:11:28,240
I don't think they realise
how ridiculous that would be.

1440
02:11:28,360 --> 02:11:30,240
- Ridiculous?
- Well, yes.

1441
02:11:30,360 --> 02:11:33,480
I mean, you live in that big house,
and your father,

1442
02:11:33,600 --> 02:11:36,600
and the factory and all.
It's a different world.

1443
02:11:36,680 --> 02:11:40,480
If I said something like that,
you'd call me a snob.

1444
02:11:40,600 --> 02:11:43,560
- I didn't mean...
- Goodbye!

1445
02:11:48,160 --> 02:11:51,160
Well, don't you want to ride up front?

1446
02:11:59,880 --> 02:12:03,320
Well, that was a fine picnic, wasn't it?

1447
02:12:06,440 --> 02:12:09,720
- Shall we have another one tomorrow?
- With Truly?

1448
02:12:09,800 --> 02:12:14,800
Well, Miss Scrumptious has a lot
of social engagements, you know.

1449
02:12:16,440 --> 02:12:19,440
Are we ever going to see Truly again?

1450
02:12:21,080 --> 02:12:23,640
Well, we'll see.

1451
02:12:30,000 --> 02:12:32,600
That's Lord Scrumptious's car.

1452
02:12:32,680 --> 02:12:35,560
- Why, I believe it is.
- I wonder what it's doing here.

1453
02:12:35,640 --> 02:12:38,320
- I don't know.
- Come on.

1454
02:12:40,080 --> 02:12:43,080
- Excuse me? Are you...?
- Good afternoon.

1455
02:12:49,440 --> 02:12:51,360
That's wiped out your cavalry.

1456
02:12:51,440 --> 02:12:55,240
But I have my second infantry
battalion attacking from the rear.

1457
02:12:55,360 --> 02:12:57,960
Attacking from the rear?
That's dashed unethical.

1458
02:12:58,080 --> 02:13:01,600
Artillery, prepare to open fire.

1459
02:13:02,200 --> 02:13:04,520
Number one battalion,
prepare to advance.

1460
02:13:04,640 --> 02:13:08,680
- What's going on?
- I've been waiting for you, young Potts.

1461
02:13:08,800 --> 02:13:12,560
- And that wiped out your artillery.
- You're a cad, Potts.

1462
02:13:12,640 --> 02:13:17,600
- What is going on here?
- Fancy you being old Bungie's son.

1463
02:13:17,680 --> 02:13:20,880
- Best batman I ever had.
- Thank you, sir.

1464
02:13:21,000 --> 02:13:25,480
My boy, allow me to introduce
to you my brigadier.

1465
02:13:25,600 --> 02:13:29,040
- Potts, how about some more tea?
- Right away, sir.

1466
02:13:29,160 --> 02:13:32,080
As for you, there's a good chance
you may be very rich.

1467
02:13:32,160 --> 02:13:33,880
What do you mean?

1468
02:13:34,000 --> 02:13:38,680
Those confounded sweets of yours.
Useless for humans, wonderful for dogs.

1469
02:13:38,800 --> 02:13:41,120
Woof Sweets, that's what we'll call 'em.

1470
02:13:41,200 --> 02:13:45,040
Canine candies.
Dogs love 'em. Make a fortune.

1471
02:13:45,160 --> 02:13:47,280
- You've done it, Daddy.
- Have I?

1472
02:13:47,360 --> 02:13:49,520
It's the posh life for us all now.

1473
02:13:49,640 --> 02:13:51,600
We're going to be rich.

1474
02:13:51,680 --> 02:13:54,320
I invented something
that actually works?

1475
02:13:54,400 --> 02:13:57,720
I wouldn't be offering you
a contract otherwise.

1476
02:13:59,320 --> 02:14:01,440
Later. Don't go away.

1477
02:14:01,560 --> 02:14:04,520
- What about the contract?
- Where are you going?

1478
02:14:04,920 --> 02:14:06,920
Daddy!

1479
02:14:10,400 --> 02:14:12,480
What's the matter with the fella?

1480
02:14:12,600 --> 02:14:16,040
He's a bit of an eccentric, sir.
A genius, of course.

1481
02:14:16,160 --> 02:14:19,880
But definitely an eccentric.

1482
02:14:20,000 --> 02:14:22,800
Can't imagine where he gets it from.

1483
